Task 5: WAF Implementation —Code ReferenceThis document contains all configuration files, custom rules, and testscripts used to implement the Web Application Firewall for the labweb application.1. Base Web ApplicationMinimal PHP endpoint used as a test surface for SQLi/XSS filteringrules./var/www/html/search.php<?php// search.php - intentionally simple, for testing WAF rules against$q = $_GET['q'] ?? '';echo "Results for: " . htmlspecialchars($q); // safe rendering atapp layer;// WAF must catchpayload before this?>Package installationsudo apt update && sudo apt install -y nginx php-fpm php-mysqlmysql-server2. ModSecurity Installationsudo apt install -y libmodsecurity3 libnginx-mod-http-modsecuritynginxsudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/modsecsudo cp /usr/share/modsecurity-crs/crs-setup.conf.example/etc/nginx/modsec/crs-setup.conf3. Nginx Configuration/etc/nginx/nginx.conf (inside the http {} block)http {modsecurity on;modsecurity_rules_file /etc/nginx/modsec/main.conf;server {listen 80;server_name yourdomain.com;root /var/www/html;index search.php index.php;location ~ \.php$ {include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php/php8.1-fpm.sock;}}}4. ModSecurity Main Config/etc/nginx/modsec/main.confInclude /etc/nginx/modsec/modsecurity.confInclude /etc/nginx/modsec/crs-setup.confInclude /usr/share/modsecurity-crs/rules/*.confInclude /etc/nginx/modsec/custom-rules.conf/etc/nginx/modsec/modsecurity.conf (key directives)SecRuleEngine DetectionOnly# Switch to "On" once audit log is clean of false positivesSecRequestBodyAccess OnSecResponseBodyAccess OffSecAuditEngine RelevantOnlySecAuditLog /var/log/modsec_audit.logSecAuditLogParts ABIJDEFHZSecAuditLogType Serial5. CRS Paranoia Level (SQLi/XSSSensitivity)/etc/nginx/modsec/crs-setup.conf (excerpt)SecAction \"id:900000,\phase:1,\nolog,\pass,\t:none,\setvar:tx.paranoia_level=2"SecAction \"id:900001,\phase:1,\nolog,\pass,\t:none,\setvar:tx.blocking_paranoia_level=2"6. Custom Rules — IP Blocking & RateLimiting/etc/nginx/modsec/custom-rules.conf# --- Block specific malicious IPs / ranges ---SecRule REMOTE_ADDR "@ipMatch 203.0.113.5,198.51.100.0/24" \"id:1001,phase:1,deny,status:403,log,\msg:'Blocked malicious IP'"# --- Basic rate limiting: >100 requests per 60s per IP ---SecAction \"id:1002,phase:1,nolog,pass,\initcol:ip=%{REMOTE_ADDR},\setvar:ip.request_count=+1,\expirevar:ip.request_count=60"SecRule IP:REQUEST_COUNT "@gt 100" \"id:1003,phase:1,deny,status:429,log,\msg:'Rate limit exceeded'"# --- Tighter rate limit on login endpoint (brute force mitigation)---SecRule REQUEST_URI "@streq /login" \"id:1004,phase:1,nolog,pass,\initcol:ip=%{REMOTE_ADDR}_login,\setvar:ip.login_count=+1,\expirevar:ip.login_count=60"SecRule IP:LOGIN_COUNT "@gt 10" \"id:1005,phase:1,deny,status:429,log,\msg:'Login rate limit exceeded',\chain"SecRule REQUEST_URI "@streq /login"7. Applying and Testing the Configsudo nginx -tsudo systemctl restart nginx# Watch the audit log while testingsudo tail -f /var/log/modsec_audit.log8. Cloudflare Custom Rule Expressions(Free Tier)Entered under Security → WAF → Custom rules in the Cloudflaredashboard.# Block a known malicious IP(ip.src eq 203.0.113.5)→ Action: Block# Block common SQLi/XSS patterns at the edge(http.request.uri.query contains "union select") or(http.request.uri.query contains "<script")→ Action: Block# Rate limit the login endpointMatch: http.request.uri.path contains "/login"Rate: 10 requests / 1 minute / IPAction: Block (for 1 hour)9. Validation / Test Script#!/bin/bash# waf_test.sh — safe validation tests against your OWN lab app onlyecho "[1] SQLi payload test"curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" \"https://yourdomain.com/search.php?q=1' UNION SELECTusername,password FROM users--"echo "[2] XSS payload test"curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" \"https://yourdomain.com/search.php?q=<script>alert(1)</script>"echo "[3] Rate limit test (150 requests)"for i in {1..150}; docurl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n""https://yourdomain.com/login"done | sort | uniq -cExpected result: early requests return 200, later requests return 403(ModSecurity/Cloudflare block) or 429 (rate limit) once thresholds arehit.
